This paper is about connections between neural models and classical machine learning approaches, specifically weighted finite state automata (WFSAs). The paper focuses on natural language processing, which is a common topic in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses recurrent neural networks, which are commonly studied in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper's focus on designing and understanding neural models suggests that it could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on formal characterization and analysis suggests that it could also be relevant to the cs.SD (Software Engineering) sub-category.
